  "prompt": "Do candles spoil?",
  "response": "Candles generally do not spoil in the same way that food does, but they can degrade over time:\n\n1. Scented candles:\n- Can lose their fragrance over time\n- Typically maintain quality for 1-2 years\n- Stored in cool, dark places last longer\n\n2. Unscented candles:\n- Can last much longer, potentially decades\n- May develop a yellowing or discoloration\n- Paraffin candles might become brittle\n\n3. Factors affecting candle condition:\n- Exposure to heat and sunlight\n- Humidity\n- Storage conditions\n- Quality of original manufacture\n\n4. Signs of candle deterioration:\n- Loss of scent\n- Discoloration\n- Cracking or separation of wax\n- Fading of color\n\n5. Storage tips:\n- Keep in cool, dry place\n- Avoid direct sunlight\n- Store in airtight container if possible\n\nWhile candles don't \"spoil\" like food, their quality and performance can decline over time.",
